{[showcards S:H4]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \CK and continue with the \CJ then \CQ, taken by South's \CA. To trick 4 South plays the \H4. What do you play?

Play the \HQ.

To see why you should play the \HQ, just visualize the result if you play low. South will finesse with dummy's \H8. If East wins his \HJ on this trick there will be 4 good \H tricks in dummy. If East withholds his \HJ then Declarer will have 3 \H winners.

Now visualize the result of playing the \HQ. Whether South takes this trick or not he cannot win more than 2 \Hs.}
[Play "W"]CK

